&lt;p&gt;Community Nurse - District Nursing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Various Hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the District Nursing Service; we are seeking to appoint highly enthusiastic and motivated individuals to join the service as a Community Staff Nurse. We are looking for enthusiastic nurses who are interested in caring for patients in their home environment. Successful applicants would be required to work independently and as part of a team and will be responsible for the provision of evidence based treatment interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Operational hours of the service are 24 hours a day 7 days per week 365 days per year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amongst your repertoire of skills, the following will be essential:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Registered General Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and caring skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent time management and organisational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be expected to be innovative and flexible to meet service need&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
